==English==
=== Etymology ===
From {{Hung.}} [[kocsi]]

According to historians the coach was named after a small Hungarian village - Kocs - which made a livelihood from cart building and transport between Vienna and Budapest. 

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-es}}

# A type of [[carriage]]
# {{sports}} A [[trainer]]
# {{UK}} A long-distance [[bus]]

